{
  "format": "tiptap/v1",
  "doc": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Why Conditionals in JSX Are Different"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "JSX only accepts "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "expressions"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " inside "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "{}"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " — not statements. This rules out "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "if"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ", "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "else"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ", "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "for"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ", and "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "while"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " directly inside the JSX tree. The result is a small set of idiomatic patterns for conditional rendering, each with different trade-offs."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "React renders "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "null"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ", "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "undefined"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ", "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "false"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ", and empty arrays as "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "nothing"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " — they produce no DOM output. This makes conditional rendering expressible as: \"return this element, or return null.\""
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "blockquote",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Every conditional rendering pattern in React is just a JavaScript expression that evaluates to either a React element or a value React skips ("
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "code"
                  }
                ],
                "text": "null"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": ", "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "code"
                  }
                ],
                "text": "false"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": ", "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "code"
                  }
                ],
                "text": "undefined"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": ")."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "attrs": {
          "src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,",
          "alt": "Diagram of four conditional rendering patterns: ternary, && short-circuit, if/else before return, and helper function",
          "title": null
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Ternary Operator: A or B"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The ternary is the most common inline conditional — use it when you have exactly two mutually exclusive outcomes:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "jsx"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "// Basic ternary\nfunction Greeting({ isLoggedIn }) {\n  return (\n    <div>\n      {isLoggedIn\n        ? <UserDashboard />\n        : <LoginPrompt />\n      }\n    </div>\n  );\n}\n\n// Ternary with null for \"show or hide\"\nfunction UserBadge({ isPremium }) {\n  return (\n    <span>\n      User\n      {isPremium ? <PremiumIcon /> : null}\n    </span>\n  );\n}\n\n// Ternary in attribute\nfunction Button({ isLoading, onClick, children }) {\n  return (\n    <button\n      onClick={isLoading ? undefined : onClick}\n      className={isLoading ? 'btn-loading' : 'btn'}\n    >\n      {isLoading ? <Spinner /> : children}\n    </button>\n  );\n}"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Nested ternaries are syntactically valid but harm readability. More than one level of nesting is a signal to extract a helper function or restructure with early returns."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "&& Short-Circuit: Show or Nothing"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "When you want to show something or nothing (no else branch), use the logical AND operator. JavaScript evaluates "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "A && B"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " as: if A is truthy, return B; otherwise return A."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "jsx"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "// Show a banner only when there's an error\nfunction Page({ error, content }) {\n  return (\n    <div>\n      {error && <ErrorBanner message={error} />}\n      <main>{content}</main>\n    </div>\n  );\n}\n\n// Multiple independent optional sections\nfunction Profile({ user }) {\n  return (\n    <div>\n      <h1>{user.name}</h1>\n      {user.bio && <p className=\"bio\">{user.bio}</p>}\n      {user.website && (\n        <a href={user.website} target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer\">\n          Website\n        </a>\n      )}\n      {user.isPremium && <PremiumBadge />}\n    </div>\n  );\n}"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The Number Zero Gotcha"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A critical trap: "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "{count && <List />}"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " renders "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "0"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " when count is 0 — because "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "0"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " is falsy but not "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "false"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " or "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "null"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ". React renders numbers as text."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "jsx"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "// BUG: renders \"0\" when items is empty\nfunction ItemList({ items }) {\n  return <div>{items.length && <ul>...</ul>}</div>;\n  // When items.length === 0:\n  // 0 && <ul> → 0 (falsy but numeric)\n  // React renders \"0\" as text\n}\n\n// FIX 1: explicit boolean conversion\nfunction ItemList({ items }) {\n  return <div>{items.length > 0 && <ul>...</ul>}</div>;\n  // items.length > 0 is a boolean — false renders nothing\n}\n\n// FIX 2: double-negation (less readable)\nfunction ItemList({ items }) {\n  return <div>{!!items.length && <ul>...</ul>}</div>;\n}\n\n// FIX 3: ternary with null\nfunction ItemList({ items }) {\n  return <div>{items.length ? <ul>...</ul> : null}</div>;\n}"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "blockquote",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Rule of thumb: only use "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "code"
                  }
                ],
                "text": "&&"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " with boolean-typed conditions (from comparison operators, "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "code"
                  }
                ],
                "text": ".includes()"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": ", "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "code"
                  }
                ],
                "text": ".some()"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": ", etc). Avoid using it with raw numbers, strings, or arrays unless you are certain they cannot be falsy-but-not-false."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "if/else Before return: Guard Clauses"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "When a component has multiple loading/error/empty states, guard clauses before the main return are the clearest solution. They use full JavaScript, not expression-only JSX:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "jsx"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "function UserProfile({ userId }) {\n  const [user, setUser] = useState(null);\n  const [loading, setLoading] = useState(true);\n  const [error, setError] = useState(null);\n\n  useEffect(() => {\n    fetchUser(userId)\n      .then(data => { setUser(data); setLoading(false); })\n      .catch(err => { setError(err.message); setLoading(false); });\n  }, [userId]);\n\n  // Guard clauses — early returns for each non-primary state\n  if (loading) return <Spinner />;\n  if (error) return <ErrorMessage>{error}</ErrorMessage>;\n  if (!user) return null;\n\n  // Main render — only reached when data is available\n  return (\n    <div className=\"profile\">\n      <h1>{user.name}</h1>\n      <p>{user.email}</p>\n    </div>\n  );\n}"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Guard clauses scale well — each branch is a separate statement. Adding a fourth or fifth state requires one more "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "if"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " line, not deeper nesting."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "if/else for Variable Binding"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Another use of pre-return conditionals: computing a variable to use in the final JSX:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "jsx"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "function SubscriptionStatus({ plan }) {\n  let badge;\n  if (plan === 'enterprise') {\n    badge = <EnterpriseBadge />;\n  } else if (plan === 'pro') {\n    badge = <ProBadge />;\n  } else {\n    badge = null; // free tier shows nothing\n  }\n\n  return (\n    <div className=\"account\">\n      <h2>Your Plan: {plan}</h2>\n      {badge}\n    </div>\n  );\n}"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "This pattern keeps the main JSX clean while handling complex branching logic above it. The variable "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "badge"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " holds a React element or "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "null"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " — both are valid JSX children."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Helper Functions for Complex Logic"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "When conditional logic is reused across multiple places, or is too complex for inline ternaries, extract it into a helper function that returns an element:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "jsx"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "// Helper function — pure, testable, reusable\nfunction renderLoadState(isLoading, error, data) {\n  if (isLoading) return <Spinner />;\n  if (error) return <ErrorBanner error={error} />;\n  if (!data?.length) return <EmptyState />;\n  return null; // caller renders the actual content\n}\n\nfunction ProductList({ products, isLoading, error }) {\n  const loadState = renderLoadState(isLoading, error, products);\n  if (loadState) return loadState;\n\n  return (\n    <ul>\n      {products.map(p => <ProductCard key={p.id} product={p} />)}\n    </ul>\n  );\n}\n\n// Or inline as a function call in JSX:\nfunction Sidebar({ mode }) {\n  function renderContent() {\n    switch (mode) {\n      case 'nav': return <NavigationMenu />;\n      case 'filters': return <FilterPanel />;\n      case 'search': return <SearchBox />;\n      default: return null;\n    }\n  }\n  return <aside>{renderContent()}</aside>;\n}"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Conditional Rendering and Component Identity"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Conditionally rendering different "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "component types"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " at the same position in the tree causes React to unmount and remount:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "jsx"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "// Different types — state is LOST on toggle\nfunction Toggle({ showA }) {\n  return (\n    <div>\n      {showA ? <ComponentA /> : <ComponentB />}\n    </div>\n  );\n  // Switching showA from true to false:\n  // ComponentA is unmounted (state destroyed), ComponentB is freshly mounted\n}\n\n// Same type at both branches — state PRESERVED\nfunction Toggle({ mode }) {\n  return (\n    <Input\n      type={mode === 'email' ? 'email' : 'text'}\n      // Switching mode: React updates the type attribute, preserves state\n    />\n  );\n}"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "If you want to hide a component while preserving its state, render it but hide it with CSS instead of removing it from the tree:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "jsx"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "// Hides visually but keeps the component mounted (state preserved)\nfunction TabPanel({ activeTab, tabs }) {\n  return (\n    <>\n      {tabs.map(tab => (\n        <div\n          key={tab.id}\n          style={{ display: tab.id === activeTab ? 'block' : 'none' }}\n        >\n          <tab.Component />\n        </div>\n      ))}\n    </>\n  );\n}"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Pattern Comparison Table"
          }
